blacklist(address _account) is the method used to add an address to the USDC blacklist.Key details:Function signature: blacklist(address _account)
Modifier: Only callable by the designated Blacklister role (currently controlled by Circle).
It emits a Blacklisted(address) event.
There is a corresponding unBlacklist(address _account) to remove an address.

Is it called on the proxy or implementation?On the proxy (0xa0b86991c6218b36c1d19d4a2e9eb0ce3606eb48).
Just like transfer, approve, transferWithAuthorization, etc., admin functions like blacklist are called on the USDC proxy contract.




accountsToBlacklist is a parameter in the initializeV2_2 (or similar upgrade) function on the implementation contract.How it works:This is not a regular function that gets called on an ongoing basis.
It is part of the one-time initialization when Circle upgraded the USDC contract to FiatTokenV2_2.
During the upgrade process, the new implementation is set on the proxy, and initializeV2_2(address[] accountsToBlacklist, string newSymbol) (or similar) is called directly on the implementation contract (or through an upgrader contract).

