Event & method decoding on Etherscan:Etherscan ties logs and decoded calls to the implementation because that's where the function logic and event signatures live.
Even though the top-level call is to the proxy, the internal execution and specific methods like transferWithAuthorization (or regular transfer/approve) appear under the implementation address.

MEV bots love this:transferWithAuthorization (EIP-3009) lets the bot pull/move USDC with a pre-signed authorization from the owner — no separate approval tx needed.
This is very common in high-frequency MEV/searcher bots for fast capital movement across many trades. 

